that we were like night and day.

1:09:55.279 --> 1:09:57.698
My life was black-and-white
before I met Sonya.

1:09:58.824 --> 1:09:59.908
She was the colour.

1:10:03.579 --> 1:10:04.997
I would have liked her.

1:10:05.080 --> 1:10:06.415
She was a force of nature.

1:10:07.541 --> 1:10:10.627
She convinced the school
to start up a programme

1:10:10.711 --> 1:10:12.254
for the kids that needed extra help.

1:10:12.337 --> 1:10:14.548
A lot of kids had problems at home

1:10:14.631 --> 1:10:17.718
or, uh, social anxieties.

1:10:18.343 --> 1:10:21.096
But by the time Sonya was done with 'em,

1:10:21.180 --> 1:10:22.764
they were reciting Shakespeare.

1:10:26.643 --> 1:10:29.104
I ran into one of her students,

1:10:30.147 --> 1:10:31.356
just the other day.

1:10:33.775 --> 1:10:35.235
A kid named Malcolm.

1:10:41.491 --> 1:10:42.910
You need more cream.

1:10:42.993 --> 1:10:44.203
Okay.

1:10:48.624 --> 1:10:52.920
We all got along fine, of course,
when we first moved in.

1:10:53.003 --> 1:10:54.296
It was like a gift.

1:10:54.379 --> 1:10:56.256
Welcome to the neighbourhood.

1:10:56.340 --> 1:10:58.342
-Hi, I'm Sonya.
-I'm Anita.

1:10:58.425 --> 1:11:01.011
Sonya and Anita were best friends.

1:11:01.094 --> 1:11:03.013
So I got my Allen keys...

1:11:03.096 --> 1:11:05.516
And Reuben and I were a lot alike.

1:11:05.599 --> 1:11:06.934
Hey! Slow down!

1:11:07.684 --> 1:11:08.894
About most things.

1:11:09.645 --> 1:11:10.646
Idiot.

1:11:10.729 --> 1:11:12.481
But people change.

1:11:12.564 --> 1:11:14.274
Or they don't change.

1:11:15.192 --> 1:11:18.237
Things happen. People drift apart.

1:11:19.196 --> 1:11:21.949
They build walls. They take offence.

1:11:23.450 --> 1:11:24.743
Who knows why.

1:11:27.412 --> 1:11:30.249
Maybe it was all the construction
that drove everybody crazy.

1:11:30.332 --> 1:11:33.210
You know, there used to be
a forest up on that hill.

1:11:33.293 --> 1:11:35.337
That's why they call it Birchwood.

1:11:35.420 --> 1:11:37.339
