Wait, no, he started it.

1:16:18.662 --> 1:16:20.998
-Ready?
-Rub it and smack!

1:16:21.707 --> 1:16:24.710
Rub it and smack! Smack! Karate chop!

1:16:35.929 --> 1:16:36.930
Huh.

1:17:01.747 --> 1:17:03.373
Wow, it's awfully quiet, huh?

1:17:08.629 --> 1:17:10.631
-Hey, guys.

1:17:10.714 --> 1:17:12.049
Hi.

1:17:12.674 --> 1:17:13.509
Hi.

1:17:14.301 --> 1:17:15.969
She was already asleep.

1:17:18.222 --> 1:17:19.515
How was it?

1:17:20.682 --> 1:17:23.310
-Fine.
-You did a good job tonight, Otto.

1:17:23.393 --> 1:17:24.937
You should pat yourself on the back.

1:17:34.571 --> 1:17:36.365
-Thank you, Otto.
-Yeah.

1:17:36.448 --> 1:17:37.699
Exit now.

1:17:37.783 --> 1:17:38.951
Have a good night.

1:17:40.160 --> 1:17:41.161
Okay.

1:17:57.261 --> 1:17:58.428
How did he do that?

1:18:05.227 --> 1:18:07.187
-Hi, Otto.
-Malcolm.

1:18:07.271 --> 1:18:11.024
You can't hear your chain rattle
when you switch gears like that?

1:18:11.108 --> 1:18:13.652
-My bike's getting old.
-Don't blame the bike.

1:18:13.735 --> 1:18:15.654
You just have to adjust your derailleur.

1:18:16.905 --> 1:18:19.533
-My what?
-Your derailleur needs adjusting.

1:18:23.203 --> 1:18:24.997
Uh, excuse me.

1:18:25.080 --> 1:18:26.832
-Hi, I'm Shari Kenzie.
-Hi.

1:18:26.915 --> 1:18:29.084
I'm a social media journalist.

1:18:29.168 --> 1:18:32.337
I'm, um, looking for Otto Anderson.

1:18:32.421 --> 1:18:34.423
Are you sure you wanna do that?

1:18:40.888 --> 1:18:44.099
Wow. It's great. That's amazing.

1:18:44.183 --> 1:18:46.351
You treat it right, it'll treat you right.

1:18:46.435 --> 1:18:48.270
Here. Keep the set.

1:18:48.353 --> 1:18:49.479
Thanks, Otto.

1:18:50.272 --> 1:18:54.776
I can't believe I'm helping you
throw crap onto people's lawns.

1:18:54.860 --> 1:18:56.195
Isn't two jobs enough?

1:18:57.279 --> 1:18:58.864
I'm saving up for a car.

1:18:58.947 --> 1:19:00.282
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

1:19:00.365 --> 1:19:01.909
What kind?

1:19:01.992 --> 1:19:03.118
Volkswagen.

1:19:11.752 --> 1:19:13.712
Young lady, you're blocking the garage.

1:19:13.795 --> 1:19:16.965
Mr Anderson? My name is Shari Kenzie.

1:19:17.049 --> 1:19:19.551
I'm a social media journalist, and I--

1:19:19.635 --> 1:19:20.969
What is that?

1:19:21.053 --> 1:19:24.640
I have an online series
called Everyday Heroes.

1:19:24.723 --> 1:19:27.726
What you did the other day
at the train station was amazing.

1:19:27.809 --> 1:19:29.144
You saved that man's life.

1:19:29.228 --> 1:19:30.646
You have the wrong guy.

1:19:31.772 --> 1:19:35.400
No, I don't. I've watched the video
at least a dozen times.

1:19:35.484 --> 1:19:36.944
-It's you.
-Video?

1:19:37.027 --> 1:19:38.362
You haven't seen it?

1:19:38.445 --> 1:19:42.157
Oh. A commuter recorded what happened
on their phone and posted it online.

1:19:42.241 --> 1:19:45.953
Someone in the comments recognised you.
That's how I tracked you down.

1:19:46.036 --> 1:19:47.955
It's gotten over a million views.

1:19:48.038 --> 1:19:49.790
A million? A million.

1:19:49.873 --> 1:19:52.167
Why can't people mind their own business?

1:19:52.251 --> 1:19:55.629
Because stories like yours are inspiring.

1:19:55.712 --> 1:19:57.840
If I could just talk to you
for a few minutes--

1:19:57.923 --> 1:20:00.342
No, now I've got too many things
I have to do.

1:20:00.425 --> 1:20:02.719
I recorded a video message
from the man you saved.

1:20:02.803 --> 1:20:03.929
You should see this.

1:20:04.012 --> 1:20:06.056
-Um... just pull it up.
-Otto! Hi!

1:20:06.932 --> 1:20:08.058
Good morning.

1:20:09.101 --> 1:20:09.977
Good morning.

1:20:11.603 --> 1:20:12.604
Uh...

1:20:12.688 --> 1:20:15.315
-So you ready for another driving lesson?

1:20:15.399 --> 1:20:17.317
-Now's not a good time.
-No?

1:20:17.401 --> 1:20:19.611
Hello? Hello? Hey, I'm still in here!

1:20:19.695 --> 1:20:21.405
-I didn't lock you in.
-Hello?

1:20:21.488 --> 1:20:23.699
Turn the knob, open the door.

1:20:23.782 --> 1:20:26.076
-Opened a door before, haven't you?

1:20:26.159 --> 1:20:27.160
Idiot.

1:20:29.788 --> 1:20:31.957
Otto! It's me.

1:20:32.040 --> 1:20:33.125
She's gone.

1:20:34.543 --> 1:20:36.503
Good. I'm not through with my rounds.

1:20:38.088 --> 1:20:39.965
"Social media journalist"?

1:20:40.048 --> 1:20:41.508
What the hell does that even mean?

1:20:42.301 --> 1:20:45.429
Buncha knotheads pointin'
a camera at themselves.

1:20:45.512 --> 1:20:47.181
I thought you handled it really well.

1:20:47.264 --> 1:20:49.308
I mean, closing her in your garage.

1:20:49.391 --> 1:20:53.020
That was, like, excellent strategy.

1:20:53.103 --> 1:20:55.898
-Good job.

1:20:58.567 --> 1:21:02.112
Otto, also, I was thinking
you've done so much for us.

1:21:02.196 --> 1:21:05.115
-I wanna do something for you too.
-I don't need anything.

1:21:05.199 --> 1:21:08.952
Well, I think you could do
with some decent food. Sometimes. No?

1:21:09.036 --> 1:21:10.120
Those cookies...

1:21:10.204 --> 1:21:11.747
The what? The "salporanz"?

1:21:11.830 --> 1:21:14.208
Those are not bad. They're not bad.

1:21:14.917 --> 1:21:16.418
And, also, I was thinking

1:21:16.502 --> 1:21:20.923
that I can help you clean out your house
and clean out the front hall in your home,

1:21:21.006 --> 1:21:24.384
and help you pack the coats and shoes
you have there of Sonya's.

1:21:24.468 --> 1:21:25.677
That's not needed.

1:21:26.386 --> 1:21:29.515
No, but it can help you move on.

1:21:29.598 --> 1:21:31.225
I don't wanna move on.

1:21:31.308 --> 1:21:33.143
She's always gonna be with you.

1:21:33.227 --> 1:21:35.270
-But you're still here.
-Ah...

1:21:35.354 --> 1:21:36.480
That's enough.

1:21:37.981 --> 1:21:41.610
When my father died,
my mother, she stopped living.

1:21:41.693 --> 1:21:43.862
-She just stopped like she used--
-Stop talking!

1:21:44.821 --> 1:21:47.282
-Stop it.
-Okay! Don't yell at me.

1:21:48.909 --> 1:21:52.663
Why can't people mind
their own business? Idiots.

1:21:53.664 --> 1:21:55.123
Interrupting me at every turn.

1:21:55.207 --> 1:21:58.502
The more they babble, the more
they drown out the memory of her voice.

1:21:59.169 --> 1:22:02.047
I don't want to clear Sonya from my life.

1:22:02.130 --> 1:22:03.507
She was everything.

1:22:03.590 --> 1:22:06.343
There was nothing before her,
and there's nothing after!

1:22:07.386 --> 1:22:08.387
I'm something.

1:22:12.432 --> 1:22:14.059
That son of a bitch!

1:22:14.852 --> 1:22:17.020
Uh-uh. No, no, no.

1:22:17.104 --> 1:22:18.689
Uh-uh-uh. Uh-uh-uh.

1:22:18.772 --> 1:22:21.441
Stop right there. You stop that car!

1:22:21.525 --> 1:22:25.028
Did you leave that gate open?
You left that gate open, didn't you?

1:22:25.112 --> 1:22:26.738
You're the only one who gives a damn.

1:22:26.822 --> 1:22:28.699
I give a damn
about people following the rules.

1:22:28.782 --> 1:22:31.159
Yes, I know. I know all about you.

1:22:31.243 --> 1:22:33.996
There's a file on you at the office.
It's this thick.

1:22:34.079 --> 1:22:35.539
I know about your wife.

1:22:35.622 --> 1:22:37.624
How you blame whatever happened to her
on everybody else.

1:22:37.708 --> 1:22:38.709
You shut up.

1:22:38.792 --> 1:22:41.420
Don't you say one more word.

1:22:41.503 --> 1:22:44.590
Take it easy, Otto.
Look, I'm not trying to upset you,

1:22:44.673 --> 1:22:47.968
but you really shouldn't be living alone.

1:22:48.051 --> 1:22:52.723
I mean, we know more about you
than you probably realise, so...

1:22:52.806 --> 1:22:55.559
Just look after that heart of yours, okay?

1:22:55.642 --> 1:22:56.935
What do you know about my heart?

1:22:57.644 --> 1:22:59.855
Hey, what do you know about my heart?!

1:22:59.938 --> 1:23:01.899
You prying bastard!

1:23:01.982 --> 1:23:03.192
Otto, Otto.

1:23:03.984 --> 1:23:07.070
Otto, what's going on?
Are you okay? Do you feel okay?

1:23:07.154 --> 1:23:09.239
You wanna help me, close the gate.

1:23:22.794 --> 1:23:24.588
Otto. Otto.

