♪ Oh, darling, make it go away ♪

1:30:41.275 --> 1:30:45.863
♪ Just make it go away now ♪

1:30:45.946 --> 1:30:47.781
That's enough now, darling.

1:30:51.952 --> 1:30:54.997
You're angry. I know.

1:30:57.124 --> 1:30:58.208
And sad.

1:31:00.127 --> 1:31:01.128
So am I.

1:31:03.630 --> 1:31:05.257
But now we have to live.

1:31:20.397 --> 1:31:21.481
What now?

1:31:27.362 --> 1:31:28.197
Malcolm.

1:31:28.280 --> 1:31:29.907
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to--

1:31:29.990 --> 1:31:31.742
I'm not gonna shoot you.

1:31:31.825 --> 1:31:32.868
What was that noise?

1:31:32.951 --> 1:31:36.079
The generator blew and the power is out.

1:31:36.163 --> 1:31:38.123
What d'ya want? It's freezing.

1:31:39.374 --> 1:31:41.835
I was hoping you might let me crash
on your couch for the night.

1:31:42.419 --> 1:31:43.795
This is not a hotel.

1:31:45.923 --> 1:31:47.633
No. I'm sorry.

1:31:47.716 --> 1:31:49.384
Why can't you go home?

1:31:52.262 --> 1:31:53.680
My dad kicked me out.

1:31:59.186 --> 1:32:00.896
There's a sofa you can use.

1:32:01.647 --> 1:32:05.025
Don't go into the dining room.
The ceiling needs repair.

1:32:05.108 --> 1:32:07.194
It's upstairs in Sonya's old study.

1:32:07.986 --> 1:32:10.072
So why did he kick you out?

1:32:10.155 --> 1:32:12.241
Because you're Malcolm now?

1:32:12.324 --> 1:32:14.326
Yeah, because I'm Malcolm.

1:32:14.409 --> 1:32:16.495
Because I dress like this.

1:32:17.246 --> 1:32:20.791
I read too much.
I don't like sports. Take your pick.

1:32:20.874 --> 1:32:23.043
He's embarrassed 'cause I'm trans.

1:32:23.126 --> 1:32:24.545
Then he's an idiot.

1:32:26.964 --> 1:32:28.257
This is you.

1:32:28.340 --> 1:32:30.008
Try not to touch anything.

1:32:30.092 --> 1:32:31.134
Okay.

1:33:30.903 --> 1:33:32.154
Well...

1:33:32.237 --> 1:33:33.780
Good morning. The power's still out

1:33:33.864 --> 1:33:36.408
so I cooked up the last of the eggs
while they're still good.

1:33:38.243 --> 1:33:39.203
Hope you don't mind.

1:33:40.329 --> 1:33:41.997
I have to do my rounds.

1:33:42.080 --> 1:33:43.832
Don't you at least want some coffee first?

1:33:46.585 --> 1:33:47.586
Yes.

1:33:54.176 --> 1:33:55.177
There you go.

1:33:56.678 --> 1:33:57.721
Uh, some eggs?

1:33:58.889 --> 1:33:59.973
I wouldn't say no.

1:34:00.682 --> 1:34:01.683
All right.

1:34:19.785 --> 1:34:20.869
That can...

1:34:22.287 --> 1:34:23.288
goes in here.

1:34:26.708 --> 1:34:27.709
Hang that up.

1:34:33.674 --> 1:34:36.051
Hey, Otto! Making your rounds.

1:34:36.134 --> 1:34:38.637
You mind if I join you?
I need to get my steps in.

1:34:38.720 --> 1:34:39.721
-Okay.

1:34:40.472 --> 1:34:41.682
-I'm Jimmy.
-Malcolm.

1:34:41.765 --> 1:34:43.183
-Nice to meet you.
-Aw, thanks.

1:34:46.103 --> 1:34:46.937
Yes.

1:34:47.688 --> 1:34:48.689
Yes.

1:34:49.898 --> 1:34:53.485
Hey, Otto, if you want to slow down,
we can 'cause my beats are up.

1:34:53.569 --> 1:34:54.570
Yes.

1:35:08.584 --> 1:35:12.629
Otto, did you hear they're moving Reuben
into assisted living this afternoon?

1:35:12.713 --> 1:35:13.881
Who is?

1:35:13.964 --> 1:35:15.924
The Dye & Merika guys.

1:35:16.008 --> 1:35:17.134
-My God.

1:35:17.217 --> 1:35:19.678
They convinced Anita to sell the house.

1:35:19.761 --> 1:35:21.680
No, they made the deal with Chris.

1:35:21.763 --> 1:35:24.433
-Chris? He can't do that.
-Yeah, he can.

1:35:24.516 --> 1:35:27.686
After Dye & Merika found out
Anita had Parkinson's,

1:35:27.769 --> 1:35:29.730
they tracked Chris down and--

1:35:29.813 --> 1:35:30.939
-Parkinson's?
-Yeah.

1:35:31.023 --> 1:35:33.984
So last year Chris convinced Anita
to give him power of attorney

1:35:34.067 --> 1:35:35.360
in case she got worse.

1:35:35.444 --> 1:35:38.447
So Dye & Merika made the deal
with Chris to buy the house.

1:35:38.530 --> 1:35:39.615
Those pricks.

1:35:41.074 --> 1:35:44.244
Wait, Anita found out
she had Parkinson's last year?

1:35:44.953 --> 1:35:46.038
No, that's not right.

1:35:46.121 --> 1:35:48.916
She would've told Sonya.
Sonya would've told me.

1:35:50.125 --> 1:35:53.879
Well, Anita and Reuben
didn't want you and Sonya to know.

1:35:53.962 --> 1:35:56.757
They said you had enough
on your plate as it is.

1:35:58.425 --> 1:35:59.510
They said that?

1:36:10.812 --> 1:36:14.066
I need to see everything
you ever got from Dye & Merika.

1:36:14.149 --> 1:36:17.236
Notices, letters. Do you have
a copy of the power of attorney?

1:36:17.319 --> 1:36:18.946
How do you know about that?

1:36:19.029 --> 1:36:20.614
-Do you have it?
-Yes.

1:36:20.697 --> 1:36:21.698
-Get it.
-Yes.

1:36:23.617 --> 1:36:28.580
And any records
of Reuben's condition and yours.

1:36:28.664 --> 1:36:30.457
Did Jimmy tell you that?

1:36:30.541 --> 1:36:31.959
Can you get it now?

1:36:32.042 --> 1:36:33.043
Yes.

1:36:39.216 --> 1:36:40.342
I've been an idiot.

1:36:42.344 --> 1:36:45.722
I got so wrapped up in my own troubles,
I stopped thinking of anyone else.

1:36:45.806 --> 1:36:48.141
And I figured
they weren't thinking about me.

1:36:49.935 --> 1:36:51.520
Friends shouldn't do that.

1:36:51.603 --> 1:36:52.604
So...

1:36:54.398 --> 1:36:56.942
This isn't easy to say
after all this time.

1:36:57.985 --> 1:36:59.111
But I'm sorry.

1:37:01.989 --> 1:37:04.157
And I will sort all this out.

1:37:17.129 --> 1:37:18.297
I need to use your phone.

1:37:20.549 --> 1:37:22.217
Why can't you use your own?

1:37:23.218 --> 1:37:25.053
Mine is disconnected at the moment.

1:37:27.306 --> 1:37:29.725
-Why?
-That doesn't matter.

1:37:29.808 --> 1:37:31.852
I just need to use your phone, okay?

1:37:33.896 --> 1:37:35.063
You know what?

1:37:35.147 --> 1:37:36.148
No.

1:37:36.231 --> 1:37:37.691
-No?
-No.

1:37:38.817 --> 1:37:41.528
You won't tell me
why your phone is disconnected?

1:37:41.612 --> 1:37:44.948
You won't tell me
why you need to use my phone?

1:37:45.032 --> 1:37:48.160
You won't tell me what happened
to you in the street yesterday?

1:37:48.827 --> 1:37:51.955
And then you went inside
and you wouldn't even open the door?

1:37:53.874 --> 1:37:55.459
You scared me, Otto.

1:37:57.211 --> 1:37:59.254
Do you know how long I was out there?

1:37:59.338 --> 1:38:02.299
And I didn't know
if something had happened to you.

1:38:03.717 --> 1:38:05.802
Or if something was gonna happen to you.

1:38:07.095 --> 1:38:10.557
And I'm sorry if I said
the wrong thing about Sonya's coats.

1:38:10.641 --> 1:38:12.059
But I was just trying to help.

1:38:13.477 --> 1:38:16.396
And you left me out there.

1:38:18.398 --> 1:38:21.193
So, no. You can't use my phone.

1:38:27.241 --> 1:38:30.577
You think your life is so hard
because everybody's an idiot

1:38:30.661 --> 1:38:32.579
and you have to do everything
on your own, right?

1:38:34.164 --> 1:38:34.998
Right?

1:38:36.333 --> 1:38:37.334
But guess what.

1:38:38.460 --> 1:38:39.670
You can't.

1:38:40.921 --> 1:38:41.922
No one can.

1:38:43.340 --> 1:38:44.967
And I think you should just be happy

1:38:45.050 --> 1:38:47.386
that someone was trying
to help you get through a crappy day.

1:38:49.054 --> 1:38:50.556
Even if they're an idiot.

1:38:51.723 --> 1:38:54.059
-So...
-The real estate bastards

1:38:54.142 --> 1:38:57.104
are trying to force
Anita and Reuben out of their home.

1:38:57.855 --> 1:38:59.398
That's why I need to use your phone.

1:39:03.193 --> 1:39:04.945
Okay, fine. Come on.

1:39:21.461 --> 1:39:23.338
We had never had a vacation.

1:39:27.718 --> 1:39:29.261
Sonya was six months pregnant.

1:39:30.554 --> 1:39:34.224
And she wanted to do something special
before the baby came.

1:39:35.017 --> 1:39:37.519
So we booked a trip to Niagara Falls.

1:39:39.563 --> 1:39:41.440
On the way back, the bus crashed.

1:39:43.233 --> 1:39:45.694
There'd been a recall on the brake lines,

1:39:45.777 --> 1:39:47.821
but the company never had them fixed.

1:39:49.489 --> 1:39:50.866
Sonya was paralyzed...

1:39:52.451 --> 1:39:54.453
and we lost our son.

1:39:58.373 --> 1:40:00.792
After three months,
she was finally able to come home.

1:40:01.877 --> 1:40:04.796
But they had started building
the new condos

1:40:04.880 --> 1:40:08.091
and the community centre
and the walkways,

1:40:08.175 --> 1:40:11.303
none of which were designed
for people in wheelchairs.

1:40:12.179 --> 1:40:14.806
The builders could have
changed their plans.

1:40:15.682 --> 1:40:20.062
But the laws weren't in place back then,
and they didn't care.

1:40:20.687 --> 1:40:21.772
I did.

1:40:21.855 --> 1:40:25.234
-We're putting in a new playground...
-I cared.

1:40:25.317 --> 1:40:28.070
-There's places for people like your wife.
-And I was so angry.

1:40:28.153 --> 1:40:31.240
What does that mean?
People like her? What does that mean?

1:40:31.323 --> 1:40:33.784
-What're you tryin' to say?!
-Get off of me!

1:40:34.493 --> 1:40:38.830
That's when they voted me out
as head of the homeowners' association.

1:40:41.041 --> 1:40:43.085
I wanted to obliterate them all.

1:40:43.168 --> 1:40:46.922
The builders, and the realtors,
and the bus company, the bus driver.

1:40:47.005 --> 1:40:48.632
I never would have let it go...

1:40:50.342 --> 1:40:51.343
but for Sonya.

1:40:52.886 --> 1:40:54.555
Sonya said we had to keep living.

1:40:57.808 --> 1:40:58.892
That's what I did.

1:41:00.519 --> 1:41:01.770
I lived for Sonya.

1:41:06.358 --> 1:41:08.026
Six months ago she passed away.

1:41:08.902 --> 1:41:09.903
Cancer.

1:41:14.157 --> 1:41:15.450
I was going to join her.

1:41:17.286 --> 1:41:19.663
That's why I had them disconnect my phone.

1:41:22.708 --> 1:41:25.794
But now I think
she wants me to keep living.

1:41:28.422 --> 1:41:31.175
And I have things to do.

1:41:35.345 --> 1:41:38.140


1:42:03.165 --> 1:42:04.875
You're wasting your time, Otto.

1:42:04.958 --> 1:42:07.419
It's a done deal. Reuben's coming with us.

1:42:07.503 --> 1:42:09.546
And if you get in our way,

1:42:09.630 --> 1:42:10.881
I'll have you arrested.

1:42:11.507 --> 1:42:14.384
-I'm not doing a thing.
-Don't you take another step.

1:42:15.302 --> 1:42:17.054
You are not taking my husband
away from me.

1:42:17.804 --> 1:42:21.308
Anita, please.
We're doing this for your own good.

1:42:21.391 --> 1:42:24.478
What you're doing
is trying to take my property.

1:42:25.354 --> 1:42:29.608
I want Reuben to stay right here
for the rest of his life,

1:42:29.691 --> 1:42:31.610
with me in our home.

1:42:31.693 --> 1:42:35.864
Okay, but who's gonna take care of Reuben
when you're no longer able to?

1:42:35.948 --> 1:42:38.367
Who's gonna take care of you? Otto?

1:42:38.450 --> 1:42:41.453
Otto's not in the best health either.
Are you, Otto?

1:42:42.579 --> 1:42:43.789
I'll take care of 'em.

1:42:45.082 --> 1:42:48.585
-What are you doing? Put that down.
-Anita and Reuben are like family to me.

1:42:48.669 --> 1:42:50.420
I'll take care of them
as long as they need.

1:42:50.963 --> 1:42:52.589
They're not your family.

1:42:52.673 --> 1:42:56.218
Uh, their son, Chris, has decided
they're not fit enough to be on their own,

1:42:56.301 --> 1:42:58.220
and so what we're doing is--

1:42:58.303 --> 1:43:01.640
Excuse me. When was the last time
Chris saw his parents?

1:43:01.723 --> 1:43:05.394
He lives in Japan.
They've been estranged for 10 years.

1:43:05.477 --> 1:43:07.771
Chris would have no idea
how his parents are doing,

1:43:07.855 --> 1:43:09.523
except for what you told him.

1:43:09.606 --> 1:43:11.441
Okay. And who are you?

1:43:11.525 --> 1:43:13.402
My name is Shari Kenzie.

1:43:13.485 --> 1:43:15.404
Social media journalist.

1:43:15.487 --> 1:43:18.282
-We're streaming live right now.
-Uh...

1:43:18.365 --> 1:43:21.785
All right, all right,
shut that camera off. You can't film this.

1:43:21.869 --> 1:43:23.662
It's a public sidewalk.

1:43:24.329 --> 1:43:26.999
You told Anita's son, Chris,
that she had Parkinson's,

1:43:27.082 --> 1:43:30.878
but Anita never told anyone
about her diagnosis.

1:43:30.961 --> 1:43:33.046
So how did you know?

1:43:33.130 --> 1:43:35.257
I'd have to check the records.

1:43:36.133 --> 1:43:38.969
Mr Anderson over there
is something of a local hero.

1:43:39.052 --> 1:43:44.266
He tells me you know details
about his private health records as well.

1:43:44.349 --> 1:43:46.143
So how are you and your company

1:43:46.226 --> 1:43:49.396
getting illegal access
to the medical records of seniors?

1:43:51.857 --> 1:43:54.067
Okay, let's go. We're done. We're done.

1:43:54.151 --> 1:43:55.903
Very nice to meet you.

1:43:55.986 --> 1:43:57.696
No, you're done. You're done!

1:43:57.779 --> 1:44:00.115
-Get that goddamn camera out of my face.
-Goodbye.

1:44:00.199 --> 1:44:02.075
-We did it!
-Oh, we did!

1:44:04.203 --> 1:44:05.454
Bye, thank you!

1:44:05.537 --> 1:44:08.457
I first uploaded Anita and Chris's story
an hour ago.

1:44:09.374 --> 1:44:11.168
Already dozens of people are saying

1:44:11.251 --> 1:44:13.962
Dye & Merika forced them
out of their homes.

1:44:14.046 --> 1:44:15.797
-That was easy.
-Yeah, goodbye.

1:44:15.881 --> 1:44:19.218
If you have a story,
share it with me at Shari_Kenzie.

1:44:19.301 --> 1:44:21.512
-I got it. I got it.

1:44:22.888 --> 1:44:25.307
Hey, you forgot to shut the gate!

1:44:25.390 --> 1:44:28.310
You see that?
He just rolled right over. Gave up.

1:44:28.393 --> 1:44:30.604
In our day, the bastards would
at least put up a fight.

1:44:32.064 --> 1:44:33.607
They haven't gotten rid of us yet.

1:44:42.950 --> 1:44:44.159
Yeah.

1:44:44.243 --> 1:44:46.453
It does feel pretty good. Doesn't it?

1:44:53.794 --> 1:44:56.547
Neighbourly neighbours,
a thing of the past?

1:44:56.630 --> 1:45:00.717
Well, I'm here with eyewitnesses
Anita and Jimmy to find out more.

1:45:00.801 --> 1:45:03.929
Jimmy, you mentioned that Anita
and Reuben are like family to you.

1:45:04.012 --> 1:45:05.681
What does that mean, exactly?

1:45:05.764 --> 1:45:08.517
Well, I have dinner at their house
nearly every single night.

1:45:12.980 --> 1:45:16.316
I know what you're waiting for.
You're ready for lunch, aren't you?

1:45:17.067 --> 1:45:18.819
I know what you want.

1:45:21.613 --> 1:45:23.156
Whoa. Here we go.

1:45:23.240 --> 1:45:25.033
You moved into this community recently.

1:45:25.117 --> 1:45:27.244
-How has that been for you?
-It's been beautiful.

1:45:27.327 --> 1:45:30.163
And your family,
to have people there that are--

1:45:30.247 --> 1:45:31.206
Yeah.

1:45:31.290 --> 1:45:33.083
-Otto?
-Will you air this in Mexico?

1:45:33.166 --> 1:45:34.168
Otto!

1:45:35.043 --> 1:45:37.171
Call an ambulance!

1:45:51.852 --> 1:45:53.854
-Ms Mendes? You can see him now.
-Yes?

1:45:53.937 --> 1:45:55.647
Yes. Yeah.

1:46:00.819 --> 1:46:03.113
Hola, Abuelo Otto.

1:46:18.045 --> 1:46:19.046
Ms Mendes?

1:46:19.630 --> 1:46:21.048
I'm Dr Ellis.

1:46:21.131 --> 1:46:23.217
Mr Anderson listed you as next of kin.

1:46:24.092 --> 1:46:26.845
Yes. Yes, that's correct.

1:46:26.929 --> 1:46:30.015
Your uncle had a close call.
Has he spoken to you about his condition?

1:46:30.849 --> 1:46:32.142
Mm...

